$ Perl regular expressions: match between

The following example matches the texts between `<ITEMS>` and `</ITEMS>`
gh|about-perl|/regular-expressions/match-between-1.pl||

Apparently, this construct is also known as → http://www.rexegg.com/regex-quantifiers.html#tempered_greed[tempered greedy token] (also → http://stackoverflow.com/a/37343088/180275[this Stackoverflow answer]).

